6 11–203.
7 (e) (1) In this subsection, “University” means the University System of
8 Maryland, Morgan State University, or St. Mary’s College of Maryland.
9 (2) Except as otherwise provided in this subsection, this Division II does
10 not apply to the University System of Maryland, Morgan State University, St. Mary’s
11 College of Maryland, or Baltimore City Community College.
12 (3) (i) A procurement by a University or Baltimore City Community
13 College shall comply with the policies and procedures developed by the University or
14 Baltimore City Community College and approved by the Board of Public Works and the
15 Administrative, Executive, and Legislative Review Committee of the General Assembly in
16 accordance with:
17 1. § 12–112 of the Education Article for the University
18 System of Maryland;
19 2. § 14–109 of the Education Article for Morgan State
20 University;
21 3. § 14–405(f) of the Education Article for St. Mary’s College
22 of Maryland; or
23 4. § 16–505.3 of the Education Article for Baltimore City
24 Community College.
25 (ii) 1. The review and approval of the Board of Public Works
26 shall be required for the following types of contracts with a value that exceeds $1,000,000
27 for a University or $500,000 for Baltimore City Community College:
28 A. capital improvements; and
29 B. services.
30 2. In its review of a contract for services or capital
31 improvements with a value that exceeds $1,000,000, the Board of Public Works may request
32 the comments of the appropriate agencies, including the Department of Budget and
33 Management and the Department of General Services.

