3 17–601.
4 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
5 (B) “APPLICABLE PERCENTAGE” MEANS THE PERCENTAGE OF TOTAL
6 LABOR HOURS OF WORK ON A COVERED PROJECT, INCLUDING CONSTRUCTION,
7 ALTERATION, AND REPAIR WORK, PERFORMED BY AN APPRENTICE OR A
8 JOURNEYWORKER ESTABLISHED UNDER § 17–602.1 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
9 [(b)] (C) “Apprenticeship training program” means an apprenticeship training
10 program that:
11 (1) is registered with, and approved by, the Apprenticeship and Training
12 Council or the U.S. Department of Labor; AND
13 (2) COMPLIES WITH THE REQUIREMENTS OF 29 C.F.R. PART 29 AND
14 PART 30.
15 [(c)] (D) “Covered craft” means a classification of workers listed in the prevailing
16 wage determination applicable to the covered project.
17 [(d)] (E) “Covered project” means a project for the construction of a public work[,
18 as defined under § 17–201 of this title, that is valued at $500,000 or more] THAT IS
19 SUBJECT TO SUBTITLE 2 OF THIS TITLE.
20 [(e)] (F) “Department” means the Maryland Department of Labor.
21 [(f)] (G) “Fund” means the State Apprenticeship Training Fund established
22 under § 17–602 of this subtitle.
23 (H) “LABOR HOURS” MEANS THE TOTAL NUMBER OF HOURS DEVOTED TO
24 THE PERFORMANCE OF CONSTRUCTION, ALTERATION, OR REPAIR WORK BY ANY
25 INDIVIDUAL AND EXCLUDES HOURS WORKED BY:
26 (1) FOREMEN;
27 (2) SUPERINTENDENTS;
28 (3) OWNERS; OR

SENATE BILL 964 7
1 (4) ANY PERSON EMPLOYED IN A BONA FIDE EXECUTIVE,
2 ADMINISTRATIVE, OR PROFESSIONAL CAPACITY, AS DEFINED IN 29 C.F.R. PART
3 541.
4 [(g)] (I) “Participates in an apprenticeship training program” means that a
5 contractor or subcontractor makes regular financial contributions for each covered craft to
6 apprenticeship training programs for covered crafts during the term of the covered project
7 that are at least equal to the hourly fringe benefit contribution rates required for
8 apprenticeship training by the applicable prevailing wage determination for the project, as
9 specified by the Secretary.
10 (J) “QUALIFIED APPRENTICE OR JOURNEYWORKER” MEANS AN
11 INDIVIDUAL WHO IS PARTICIPATING IN AN APPRENTICESHIP TRAINING PROGRAM.
12 [(h)] (K) “Secretary” means the Secretary of Labor.
13 17–601.1.
14 (A) THIS SUBTITLE APPLIES ONLY TO CONTRACTORS AND
15 SUBCONTRACTORS WHO EMPLOY FOUR OR MORE INDIVIDUALS TO PERFORM WORK
16 ON A COVERED PROJECT.
17 (B) NOTHING IN THIS SUBTITLE MAY PREEMPT A LOCAL LAW OR POLICY
18 PROVIDING FOR ADDITIONAL SKILLED AND TRAINED WORKFORCE REQUIREMENTS
19 ON PUBLIC WORKS PROJECTS.
20 17–602.
21 (a) There is a State Apprenticeship Training Fund in the Department.
22 (b) The Fund consists of:
23 (1) payments made by contractors or subcontractors in accordance with
24 this subtitle and Subtitle 6A of this title;
25 (2) penalties collected as a result of violations of this subtitle and Subtitle
26 6A of this title; and
27 (3) penalties collected as a result of violations of Title 14, Subtitle 8 of this
28 article.
29 (c) The Fund is a special, nonlapsing fund that is not subject to § 7–302 of this
30 article.
31 (d) The State Treasurer shall hold the Fund separately, and the Comptroller shall
32 account for the Fund.

8 SENATE BILL 964
1 (e) The Secretary shall use money in the Fund to:
2 (1) promote preapprenticeship programs and other workforce development
3 programs in the State’s public secondary schools and community colleges that assist
4 students in preparing for and entering apprenticeship training programs; and
5 (2) pay any costs associated with carrying out the provisions of this subtitle
6 and Subtitle 6A of this title or Title 14, Subtitle 8 of this article.
7 17–602.1.
8 (A) FOR CONSTRUCTION ON A COVERED PROJECT FOR WHICH A PUBLIC
9 BODY ADVERTISES FOR BIDS OR PROPOSALS FOR A PUBLIC WORKS CONTRACT ON
10 OR AFTER JANUARY 1, 2027, THE APPLICABLE PERCENTAGE IS 20%.
11 (B) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31, 2027, AND EACH DECEMBER 31
12 THEREAFTER, THE SECRETARY SHALL SET THE APPLICABLE PERCENTAGE THAT
13 WILL APPLY FOR THE FOLLOWING CALENDAR YEAR.
14 (C) THE SECRETARY MAY ALTER THE APPLICABLE PERCENTAGE FOR A
15 COVERED PROJECT TO MEET ANY RATIO REQUIREMENTS NECESSARY FOR
16 APPRENTICE OR JOURNEYWORKER SUPERVISION IN THE COVERED CRAFT.
17 17–603.
18 (a) A contractor that is awarded a procurement contract for a covered project shall
19 provide to a unit, as a condition of receiving the contract, written verification that:
20 (1) the contractor [participates in an apprenticeship training program for
21 each covered craft in which it will employ persons for the covered project] IS EMPLOYING
22 THE NUMBER OF QUALIFIED APPRENTICES OR JOURNEYWORKERS FOR A COVERED
23 PROJECT NECESSARY TO MEET THE APPLICABLE PERCENTAGE FOR THE COVERED
24 PROJECT; OR
25 (2) the contractor will make payments to the Fund[; or
26 (3) the contractor will make payments in amounts determined under §
27 17–605 of this subtitle to a registered apprenticeship program or to an organization that
28 has registered apprenticeship programs for the purpose of supporting these programs].
29 (b) The written verification required under subsection (a) of this section shall be
30 provided by a contractor to the unit responsible for the project before the contractor
31 commences performance under the procurement contract.

